bilingual.source: Her approach to the problem was very philosophical.
bilingual.target: 她解决问题的方法非常哲学的。

bilingual.source: He enjoys reading philosophical books in his free time.
bilingual.target: 他喜欢在空闲时间阅读哲学的书籍。

bilingual.source: They had a philosophical discussion about the meaning of life.
bilingual.target: 他们进行了关于生命意义的哲学的讨论。

bilingual.source: The novel explores philosophical themes such as existence and truth.
bilingual.target: 这部小说探讨了存在和真理等哲学的主题。

bilingual.source: The professor gave a philosophical lecture on the nature of reality.
bilingual.target: 教授做了一场关于现实本质的哲学的讲座。

bilingual.source: He said it was a philosophical fiction.
The book is more than a philosophical exercise.
bilingual.target: 这本书也充满了哲学的味道。
听起来多么哲学的一个词啊，“万物

bilingual.source: In philosophical jargon, this is a question from metaphysics.
bilingual.target: 我由什么构成？在哲学的术语中，这个是形而上学的问题。

bilingual.source: Philosophical methodologies are need in analyzing and thinking.
bilingual.target: 需要用哲学的方法去分析、思考.

yingyinNormal.en: And this is the crucial part of our philosophical reflection we have today.
yingyinNormal.zh: 这也是我们目前最重要的哲学思辨范畴

yingyinNormal.en: First, windows. Conventional. Open, closed. Open, closed. Halfway open. Or halfway closed, depending on your philosophical bent.
yingyinNormal.zh: 首先，窗户，很常见。打开，关上。打开，关上。开一半，或者说关一半，这取决于你的哲学取向。

yingyinNormal.en: While that perspective might sound very philosophical, I found that it was very practical, because it showed me how I could deal with my own realities in a better way.
yingyinNormal.zh: 这种看法听起来可能很哲学，但我觉得非常实用，因为我看到了处理现实的更好的方法。
